### Stray punit-sentinel working-directory specs
# Some SentinelMainTest cases clear `punit.spec.dir` via System.clearProperty,
# causing SentinelExperimentExecutor.resolveSpecOutputDir() to fall through to
# the relative default `punit/specs` — which resolves to the module root when
# run via Gradle. Tracked as a test-hygiene follow-up; ignored here to keep
# the source tree clean.
punit-sentinel/punit/

### Orchestrator-managed
# Requirements / design / planning material for punit lives in
# javai-orchestrator from 0.7.0 onwards, not in this repository.
# The block below prevents accidental re-introduction.
/plan/

### Generated PUnit experiment output
# Explore and Optimize outputs default to build/punit/{explorations,optimizations}
# (already covered by the build/ entry above).
#
# Measure specs are inputs to subsequent @ProbabilisticTest runs and are
# intended to be committed under src/test/resources/punit/specs/ in downstream
# projects. In this repo, punit-junit5's own TestKit regenerates them on every
# test run; its build.gradle.kts redirects them to build/ to avoid source-tree
# churn, so no entry is needed here.
#
# Legacy paths — some pre-0.6.0 contents may remain in source trees until
# purged. The entries below prevent accidental re-staging if old content
# lingers on disk after a clean:
**/src/test/resources/punit/explorations/
**/src/test/resources/punit/optimizations/
